  <h2>My Roadmap for 2025</h2>
  <p>
    Over the last few years, I have evolved from a curious Ruby beginner to a DevOps-focused engineer deploying scalable, secure infrastructures. In 2024, I modernised a 13-year-old Rails application by migrating it from EC2 to ECS Fargate, learning firsthand how containerisation can streamline operations by eliminating the need for manual server management. Meanwhile, <strong>Linkarooie</strong>, my side project, has served as a proving ground for Rails upgrades and innovative deployment strategies.
  </p>
  <p>
    As I look to 2025, my focus has sharpened. Alongside doubling down on <strong>AWS ECS/Fargate</strong> and refining my Docker container workflows, I am now diving deeper into distributed systems theory, advanced AWS architecture, and system design. I'm also committed to sharing my journey through technical writing and speaking engagements—steps that reflect my drive to become a recognised industry innovator.
  </p>

