            With OG image fixes and the Rails 8 upgrade complete, the next step is transitioning from invite-only signups to email validation, improving accessibility and maintaining security.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          Leverage Docker container workflows with <strong>Kamal on DigitalOcean</strong> for deployments, harnessing a streamlined approach that eliminates the need for manual server management.
        </li>
        <li>
          Scale performance with caching (Redis) and database optimisations so Linkarooie can handle an expanding user base.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Upgrade Linkarooie to Ruby 3.4</strong>, taking advantage of new language features and performance improvements introduced in the latest release.
